text: William Stephen (1 April 1928 â€“ 24 August 2020) was an Australian rules footballer. He played with Fitzroy Football Club. He also coached Fitzroy and Essendon. He was born in Sydney. Stephens was captain / coach of Yarrawonga in the Ovens & Murray Football League from 1958 to 1963, then was their non playing coach in 1964. Stephen died on 24 August 2020 at the age of 92.Vale Bill Stephen ==References== Category:1928 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers Category:Sportspeople from Victoria (Australia)
